Jack Liu is one of China's earliest experts in computer viruses and network security technology, having founded two companies in information security and software technology sectors, where he also served as chairman.

In 2004, he founded Beijing Ri-yue-guang-hua Software Ltd., where he served as the legal representative, chairman, and CTO, successfully developing Guanghua antivirus software and its mobile version before Tencent's acquisition.
Jack joined Tencent in 2010 as Assistant General Manager, leading advancements in security technology and becoming a T4 Expert within the Tencent Group, focusing on various research areas like big data, artificial intelligence, and e-commerce logistics. In 2016, he took on the role of CTO at Zhongshi Jinqiao International Media Group, working on internet advertising systems and other projects.
